\newlabel{sub@fig:class_distribution}{{a}{10}{Top-level class distribution across all 135{,}751 VGP TE sequences. Unannotated sequences (``None'') dominate at 62.3\%; among annotated classes LTR (18.8\%), LINE (10.4\%) and DNA (7.9\%) are the principal categories. Minor classes (SINE, PLE, RC $<$0.5\%) are shown in the legend}{figure.caption.3}{}}
\newlabel{fig:superfamily_distribution}{{1b}{10}{Superfamily abundances within each top-level class (top 30, excluding None). LTR/Gypsy and LINE/L1 are the most frequent. Among DNA transposons, hAT and TcMar-Tc1 dominate; rare superfamilies (${<}200$ samples) are the main source of fine-grained classification difficulty}{figure.caption.3}{}}
